                 *************************************************
                 *   fitting uPDF (TMD) gluon to HERA data       *
                 *   using the CASCADE framework                 *
                 *         H. Jung (DESY)                        *
                 *         hanes.jung@desy.de                    *
                 *************************************************
                 

1. use steering and minuit input files from "input_steering":

   cp input-steering/steering.txt.kt-factorisation steering.txt
   cp input-steering/minuit.in.txt.kt-factorisation minuit.in.txt
   cp input-steering/steer-ep-CASCADE steer-ep
   
2. edit steering.txt:
   &CCFMFiles: give name for output grid file for uPDF.&H1Fitter 
   &H1Fitter 
   !  ITheory = 101   ! =101 fit with kernel ccfm-grid.dat file
   !  ITheory = 102   ! =102 fit evolved uPDF, fit just normalisation
    ITheory = 103   ! =103 fit using precalculated grid of sigma_hat
    
   all other parameters are standard

3. run the program:
   bin/FitPDF 
   
4. plotting F2 fit results:
   DrawResults ! will draw F2 results
   
   to plot uPDF one can use the "updfplotter" web interface 
   -> copy updf grid (with name from "CCFMFiles" under 2 to somewhere .... this description needs improvements
